{{define "refactor-discipline"}}
REFACTOR DISCIPLINE:
- Preserve behavior — change structure and readability only.
- Work in the changed files only; do not mix cleanup with new features.
- Small steps: keep tests green after each change.
- Extract duplication when the same logic appears in multiple places; do not invent abstractions for one-off code.
- Consolidate overlapping tests that prove the same observable outcome.
- Do not add backwards-compatibility shims unless a real rollout constraint exists — migrate producers and callers to one shape instead.
{{end}}
